  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Breakfast is buffet style with hot and cold options. Dinner is three courses with a choice of main course (drinks not included). The starters and desserts are served buffet style.</p>
<p>The bar is closed in the afternoons but guests can enjoy drinks at the properties 4 star sister hotel located next door (payable locally).</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>The charming Pension Angelo is small and homely, so you'll feel well looked after when you stay here. The property has a great location in <a data-udi="umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8}" title="Corvara &amp; Colfosco">Covara</a>, the main lifts are nearby so you can easily get onto the slopes each day and at the end of the day there is no rush, as you can ski virtually back to the door. </p>
<h2>Warm and Cosy</h2>
<p>The cosy Pension Angelo is a great base for your next <a data-udi="umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902" href="/{localLink:umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902}" title="Italy">Italian</a> ski holiday. The nearest ski lift, the Arlara chair lift, gives you access to some lovely cruisy blues and reds, ideal for warming up your legs. If you want to get to the centre, all you need to do is hop on the free resort bus, or if you want to walk it's only 15 minutes to town.</p>
<p>The cosy and spacious rooms are furnished in a traditional alpine style with wonderful views of the Dolomites and there is a small wellness area available for guests to use. The food at the hotel is hearty and filling, each morning start your day with a buffet breakfast including a classic continental offering, and return to a tasty homemade meal for dinner. </p>
<h2>Spa facilities</h2>
<p>After a day on the slopes, there is a small wellness area available for you to use with <span>a sauna and steam room - perfect for soothing any achy ski legs. Guests </span>staying at the Pension Angelo can also use the facilities at the <a data-udi="umb://document/61fdc3abe9494a68ae9a0671dc3fd74f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/61fdc3abe9494a68ae9a0671dc3fd74f}" title="Sporthotel Panorama (Corvara)">Sporthotel Panorama</a> for a local fee. Have a dip in the panoramic indoor pool, or enjoy the varied spa facilities including a Kneipp, <span>Finnish sauna, Turkish steam bath, crystal sauna, hayshed sauna, and infrared sauna. For the ultimate treat, book a massage or treatment with the therapists. </span>The Panorama Bar is a great spot to enjoy an aperitif before heading back for dinner, where you can enjoy tasty homemade dinners. The spa, pool area and any drinks / snacks at the Sporthotel are payable locally.</p>
<h2>Guided Skiing</h2>
<p>From the Sporthotel Panorama, you can join guided ski excursions on a Thursday and a snow-shoe walking tour every Tuesday.</p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Pension Angelo the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
